explanation: The solution uses dynamic programming to find the minimum number of changes required to divide the string into k palindromic substrings. It iterates over all possible substrings and counts the number of changes required to make each substring a palindrome. The dp array stores the minimum number of changes required to divide the string into j palindromic substrings up to index i. The countChanges function calculates the number of changes required to make a substring a palindrome.

